text: Like this one
Man, budget deckbuilding is hard. I don't know how people do it.
My decks usually only cost me about <$50
.... though they end up being worth >$5000
Yeah that is where I am at
But right now I am trying to come in under budget and I am swearing at my monitor because Ponder is $4
I'm guessing you already used Opt, then>?
Yeah
I think we are scrapping the format
We were originally going to do upgrade kits that you could add to a guild kit to make an edh deck
But there are some real boat anchors in the guild kits

It is easy enough to make the decks functional, but to make them good you have to cut a lot of stuff, and once you start cutting you have to come to terms with the fact that you can probably do an entire deck for the upgrade budget and toss the guild kits entirely
So I think we are just going to do a set budget with ravnica lore commanders
Dude, tons of good not-Ponders
Telling Time
Impulse
Etc

Our audience is very much locked into that mindset
So when we do budget stuff it is optimized budget stuff that they are expecting
so you're looking for good cards that are currently underpriced
congrats, you're a speculator!
you did it!
I will take priced appropriately but underplayed over underpriced any day
Scrapping the guild kit idea is freeing though
